      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-04T23:49:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok. A new version using two different methods:\n\ncompactor.addPack(DfsPackDescription);\ncompactor.addReftable(DfsPackDescription);\n\nIt verifies the description has the expected field. Here the risk is that the caller add the pack to one but not the other, even when he wants both.\n\nIn a follow up change I try with (I think) a safer API:\nenum AddFlag { OBJECTS_AND_REFTABLES, ONLY_REFTABLES, ONLY_OBJECTS)\ncompactor.add(desc, ONLY_REFTABLES);\n\nrequiring the packs to have the requested segments.",
      "parentUuid": "1b3f4ff3_035d4b48",
      "revId": "45f06fe658c32c235184fc5050450d3212f828a9",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
